19.1.1 Enriched transforms
The enriched transform variants extend beyond structural changes (rename, add, drop) to semantic transforms that carry computation:

CoerceSort changes a sort’s value kind (e.g., string to int) and installs an expression that performs the coercion at migration time. The coercion expression is a term in the panproto-expr expression language.
MergeSorts combines two sorts into one (e.g., firstName + lastName to fullName), with a merger expression that specifies how to combine values.
AddSortWithDefault adds a sort with a default value expression, used when a new field needs a computed default for existing data.
AddDirectedEquation / DropDirectedEquation manage directed equations (rewrite rules) that specify computation direction for equational rewrites.



19.1.2 Cascading Drops
DropSort cascades: removing a sort also removes all operations that reference it (as input or output) and all equations that reference those operations. DropOp similarly cascades to equations. This ensures that the resulting theory is always well-formed.
